         <div type="traslation">
            <head>Translation</head>
            <p>In this day of the Kollam year 876, month of Āvaṇi, 5th day, Monday, third [lunar
               day] (tutikai), constellation of Maka, the Kūrmapurāṇam was completed, written by the
               hand of Cokkaliṅkaṉ son of Poṉṉ-ampala-tēvar, who is the beloved son (kātal-puttiraṉ)
               of Cantiracēkaraceṉṉavīramūrtti (as for °ceṉṉa° read °caṉṉa°), who is the student
               (cīṣar) of Vīracaivakaṟttācāriyaṉ [i.e.] Caivacittāntaṉ [proponent of] the
               unqualified (°nikkuṇa°, read °nirkuṇa°) manifestation of Brahman (ticai-muka°), who
               is the assistant/devotee (?) (kāriyakattar, emend into kāriyakarttar) of
               Revaṇāccittayar (conj. for evaṇāccittayar).</p>
         </div>
